1572 <div>

1573 <h2>

1574 <strong>Find the Ideal Bathtub&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;

1575 </h2>

1576 <p>Vevano Home offers a wide selection of&nbsp;high-quality, stylish bathtubs in various&nbsp;sizes and materials. Whether you're looking for a timeless cast iron freestanding tub or a sleek modern drop-in, we've got you covered. Not sure what tub is best for you? We can help with that too! Here's everything you need to know about tub sizes, shapes, materials, and more&nbsp;so you can find the ideal tub for your bathroom.</p>

1577 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1578 <h3>Bathtub Size</h3>

1579 <p>Lets start with the size of your bathtub. Some may prefer an above-average length instead of a deeper soaking depth. If you are a tall person that enjoys laying back and relaxing in your tub, you may want to choose a length over depth. Bathtubs come in 4ft, 5ft, and 6ft lengths.</p>

1580 <p>On the other hand, if you prefer to have a deeper bathtub, allowing you to emerge yourself in the water fully, you will probably want to prioritize depth over length. Some people also enjoy deeper tubs because their kids or pets can fit inside as well. A standard bathtub measures 1420 inches. Whatever you prefer, there is an option for you, and our guide on

1581 <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/standard-tub-size-measurement-guide/">how to measure a bathtub</a> can help!

1582 </p>

1583 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1584 <h3>Types of Bathtubs</h3>

1585 <p>As you search for a new tub, it helps to understand the five main types of bathtubsdrop-in, alcove, freestanding, whirlpool, and walk-in bathtubs. All of these bathtubs are very different and have unique features.</p>

1586 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1587 <h4>

1588 <span style="font-size: 18px;">

1589 <a href="https://vevano.com/catalog/showers-and-tubs-drop-in-bathtubs/">Drop-in Bathtub</a>

1590 </span>

1591 </h4>

1592 <p>This particular type of bathtub is your typical rectangular-shaped bathtub with angular lines. Drop-in bathtubs are tubs dropped in a frame or structure, featuring a rim that goes around the top of the tub. You can customize your drop-in bathtub by selecting the material you would like the rim to be made of; most people prefer tile or stone. These bathtubs are ideal for a childrens bathroom because of its shape and ease of getting in and out.</p>

1593 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1594 <h4>

1595 <span style="font-size: 18px;">

1596 <a href="https://vevano.com/catalog/showers-tubs-alcove-bathtubs/">Alcove Bathtub</a>

1597 </span>

1598 </h4>

1599 <p>An alcove bathtub is most known to be in the corner of a bathroom and is known for the way it is installed. These beautiful bathtubs are installed into a recess in a bathroom, often against a wall or in the corner. Since these tubs are designed to fit between three furnished walls, its not uncommon to see a shower curtain on the fourth wall. Alcove tubs and drop-in tubs are very similar; however, alcove tubs require fewer steps during installation.</p>

1600 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1601 <h4>

1602 <span style="font-size: 18px;">

1603 <a href="https://vevano.com/catalog/showers-and-tubs-freestanding-bathtubs/">Freestanding Bathtub</a>

1604 </span>

1605 </h4>

1606 <p>

1607 <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/best-freestanding-tubs/">Freestanding bathtubs</a> are all the rave these days. Freestanding bathtubs add a modern or contemporary look to your bathroom, making it look sleek and updated. However, if youre going for an antique-looking freestanding tub, clawfoot bathtubs would be a great option.

1608 </p>

1609 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1610 <h4>

1611 <span style="font-size: 18px;">Whirlpool Bathtubs</span>

1612 </h4>

1613 <p>A whirlpool bathtub is known for its jets that help relax and massage the muscles. So if youre looking for a relaxing bathing experience, this may be the tub for you.</p>

1614 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1615 <h4>

1616 <span style="font-size: 18px;">Walk-in Bathtubs</span>

1617 </h4>

1618 <p>This type of tub is designed for those who have trouble getting in and out of a regular bathtub. Walk-in bathtubs have grab bars that help avoid hazards like slipping and falling. Seats are also commonly found in this type of bathtub because they take pressure off the legs. A walk-in bathtub is different because there is more vertical space in the tub instead of horizontal space.</p>

1619 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1620 <h3>Bathtub Materials</h3>

1621 <p>There are various materials that bathtubs are made out of, but we will cover three of the most common materials here. These materials include porcelain, fiberglass, and acrylic. Its essential to understand the characteristics of each material so that you know

1622 <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/how-to-clean-a-bathtub/">how to clean your bathtub</a>and how best to maintain it over time. For a deeper dive into bathtub materials, check out our

1623 <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/best-bathtub-materials/">best bathtub materials</a> comparison article.

1624 </p>

1625 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1626 <h4>

1627 <span style="font-size: 18px;">Steel Bathtubs</span>

1628 </h4>

1629 <p>Steel bathtubs are sometimes referred to as porcelain tubs because the steel is covered in porcelain enamel. (On a similar note, cast iron tubs are also typically covered in porcelain, which is why they are known as enameled cast iron tubs.) Steel tubs generally are well-protected by this porcelain enamel, which is both stain and scratch-resistant and easy to clean. However, steel tubs dont retain heat well and are prone to chipping if a heavy object falls on its surface.</p>

1630 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1631 <h4>

1632 <span style="font-size: 18px;">Cast Iron Bathtubs</span>

1633 </h4>

1634 <p>Though one of the heaviest tubs you can buy, enameled cast iron tubs are incredibly durable, resistant to stains, scratches, and chips. Cast iron tubs are especially known for their excellent heat retention. With proper maintenance, your cast iron tub can last you for decades to come.</p>

1635 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1636 <h4>

1637 <span style="font-size: 18px;">Fiberglass Bathtubs</span>

1638 </h4>

1639 <p>Fiberglass tubs are made from fiberglass-reinforced plastic molded into the shape of a bathtub. These tubs are coated with a layer of gelcoat resin, which provides a high-quality finish and makes the surface easy to clean. Fiberglass is also a lightweight material, making it easy to move and install your tub.</p>

1640 <p>However, due to the nature of this lightweight material, fiberglass is also one of the most brittle bathtub materials on the market, cracking often. As a result, fiberglass tubs are generally less expensive than porcelain and acrylic tubs. In addition, the use of standard cleaning products on fiberglass also tends to discolor the surface over time. So, although this is one of the least expensive bathtub materials, keep in mind the long-term cost of buying a fiberglass tub.</p>

1641 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1642 <h4>

1643 <span style="font-size: 18px;">Acrylic Bathtubs</span>

1644 </h4>

1645 <p>Acrylic is a combination of materials like stabilizers, resins, and fillers. Acrylic is often reinforced with fiberglass, making it a bit pricier than fiberglass tubs but more durable. In addition, acrylic is a non-porous material, which means that it will not absorb any excess water in your bathtub, helping it to avoid cracking. This non-porous material also helps with heat retention, keeping the water in your tub warmer for longer.</p>

1646 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1647 <h3>Other Features to Consider</h3>

1648 <p>Weve talked about bathtubs sizes, shapes, and materials, but now its time to cover a few other features that affect your bathtub. If you would like a bathtub with a bit more support for your back while relaxing, try out a bathtub with lumbar support. If you are looking for a spa-like tub, you can purchase a bathtub with jets or a heated surface. You will also want to decide with what material you would like to finish your bathtub. The most common finish is a high-gloss white finish.</p>

1649 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1650 <h3>Drain Stopper</h3>

1651 <p>Along with the features listed above, youll want to think about the drain stopper you would like. There are five drain stoppers:</p>

1652 <ul>

1653 <li>

1654 <strong>Toe-Touch:</strong>You can open and close the train with the touch of your toe

1655 </li>

1656 <li>

1657 <strong>Push-Pull:</strong>The traditional pull-up knob in the middle to push it down and pull it to open

1658 </li>

1659 <li>

1660 <strong>Flip-It:</strong>You flip a toggle that will open or close, and you move the toggle from side to side

1661 </li>

1662 <li>

1663 <strong>Pop-Up:</strong>An internal rod moves to raise or lower the stopper

1664 </li>

1665 <li>

1666 <strong>Trip-Lever:</strong> An internal plunger stops water flow in the drain

1667 </li>

1668 </ul>

1669 <p>All of these drain stoppers are great options, so the one that you decide for your new tub will be up to you and your personal preference.</p>

1670 <p>&nbsp;</p>

1671 <h3>Whats Best For You?</h3>

1672 <p>We know theres a lot to understand when learning about bathtubs, but it doesnt need to be overwhelming. Refer back to this as your guide when it comes to any questions about bathtubs. If you have additional questions, dont hesitate to contact our designers. You can consult with our virtual interior designers by calling 855.483.2629 or email us your questions at design@vevano.com. Wed love to hear from you and help you with your bathroom remodeling!</p>

2343"css":"","html":"\u003ch2\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFind the Ideal Bathtub\u0026nbsp;

2344\u003c/strong\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2345\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eVevano Home offers a wide selection of\u0026nbsp;

2346high-quality, stylish bathtubs in various\u0026nbsp;

2347sizes and materials. Whether you\u0026#39;

2348re looking for a timeless cast iron freestanding tub or a sleek modern drop-in, we\u0026#39;

2349ve got you covered. Not sure what tub is best for you? We can help with that too! Here\u0026#39;

2350s everything you need to know about tub sizes, shapes, materials, and more\u0026nbsp;

2351so you can find the ideal tub for your bathroom.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2352\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eBathtub Size\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLet\u0026rsquo;

2353s start with the size of your bathtub. Some may prefer an above-average length instead of a deeper soaking depth. If you are a tall person that enjoys laying back and relaxing in your tub, you may want to choose a length over depth. Bathtubs come in 4ft, 5ft, and 6ft lengths.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOn the other hand, if you prefer to have a deeper bathtub, allowing you to emerge yourself in the water fully, you will probably want to prioritize depth over length. Some people also enjoy deeper tubs because their kids or pets can fit inside as well. A standard bathtub measures 14\u0026ndash;

235420 inches. Whatever you prefer, there is an option for you, and our guide on \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/resource-center/standard-tub-size-measurement-guide/\"\u003ehow to measure a bathtub\u003c/a\u003e can help!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2355\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eTypes of Bathtubs\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAs you search for a new tub, it helps to understand the five main types of bathtubs\u0026mdash;

2356drop-in, alcove, freestanding, whirlpool, and walk-in bathtubs. All of these bathtubs are very different and have unique features.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2357\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2358\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/showers-and-tubs-drop-in-bathtubs/\"\u003eDrop-in Bathtub\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis particular type of bathtub is your typical rectangular-shaped bathtub with angular lines. Drop-in bathtubs are tubs dropped in a frame or structure, featuring a rim that goes around the top of the tub. You can customize your drop-in bathtub by selecting the material you would like the rim to be made of;

2359 most people prefer tile or stone. These bathtubs are ideal for a children\u0026rsquo;

2360s bathroom because of its shape and ease of getting in and out.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2361\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2362\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/showers-tubs-alcove-bathtubs/\"\u003eAlcove Bathtub\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAn alcove bathtub is most known to be in the corner of a bathroom and is known for the way it is installed. These beautiful bathtubs are installed into a recess in a bathroom, often against a wall or in the corner. Since these tubs are designed to fit between three furnished walls, it\u0026rsquo;

2363s not uncommon to see a shower curtain on the fourth wall. Alcove tubs and drop-in tubs are very similar;

2364 however, alcove tubs require fewer steps during installation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2365\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2366\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/showers-and-tubs-freestanding-bathtubs/\"\u003eFreestanding Bathtub\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/resource-center/best-freestanding-tubs/\"\u003eFreestanding bathtubs\u003c/a\u003e are all the rave these days. Freestanding bathtubs add a modern or contemporary look to your bathroom, making it look sleek and updated. However, if you\u0026rsquo;

2367re going for an antique-looking freestanding tub, clawfoot bathtubs would be a great option.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2368\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2369\"\u003eWhirlpool Bathtubs\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA whirlpool bathtub is known for its jets that help relax and massage the muscles. So if you\u0026rsquo;

2370re looking for a relaxing bathing experience, this may be the tub for you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2371\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2372\"\u003eWalk-in Bathtubs\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis type of tub is designed for those who have trouble getting in and out of a regular bathtub. Walk-in bathtubs have grab bars that help avoid hazards like slipping and falling. Seats are also commonly found in this type of bathtub because they take pressure off the legs. A walk-in bathtub is different because there is more vertical space in the tub instead of horizontal space.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2373\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eBathtub Materials\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere are various materials that bathtubs are made out of, but we will cover three of the most common materials here. These materials include porcelain, fiberglass, and acrylic. It\u0026rsquo;

2374s essential to understand the characteristics of each material so that you know \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/resource-center/how-to-clean-a-bathtub/\"\u003ehow to clean your bathtub \u003c/a\u003eand how best to maintain it over time. For a deeper dive into bathtub materials, check out our \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/resource-center/best-bathtub-materials/\"\u003ebest bathtub materials\u003c/a\u003e comparison article.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2375\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2376\"\u003eSteel Bathtubs\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSteel bathtubs are sometimes referred to as porcelain tubs because the steel is covered in porcelain enamel. (On a similar note, cast iron tubs are also typically covered in porcelain, which is why they are known as enameled cast iron tubs.) Steel tubs generally are well-protected by this porcelain enamel, which is both stain and scratch-resistant and easy to clean. However, steel tubs don\u0026rsquo;

2377t retain heat well and are prone to chipping if a heavy object falls on its surface.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2378\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2379\"\u003eCast Iron Bathtubs\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThough one of the heaviest tubs you can buy, enameled cast iron tubs are incredibly durable, resistant to stains, scratches, and chips. Cast iron tubs are especially known for their excellent heat retention. With proper maintenance, your cast iron tub can last you for decades to come.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2380\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2381\"\u003eFiberglass Bathtubs\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFiberglass tubs are made from fiberglass-reinforced plastic molded into the shape of a bathtub. These tubs are coated with a layer of gelcoat resin, which provides a high-quality finish and makes the surface easy to clean. Fiberglass is also a lightweight material, making it easy to move and install your tub.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, due to the nature of this lightweight material, fiberglass is also one of the most brittle bathtub materials on the market, cracking often. As a result, fiberglass tubs are generally less expensive than porcelain and acrylic tubs. In addition, the use of standard cleaning products on fiberglass also tends to discolor the surface over time. So, although this is one of the least expensive bathtub materials, keep in mind the long-term cost of buying a fiberglass tub.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2382\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2383\"\u003eAcrylic Bathtubs\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAcrylic is a combination of materials like stabilizers, resins, and fillers. Acrylic is often reinforced with fiberglass, making it a bit pricier than fiberglass tubs but more durable. In addition, acrylic is a non-porous material, which means that it will not absorb any excess water in your bathtub, helping it to avoid cracking. This non-porous material also helps with heat retention, keeping the water in your tub warmer for longer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2384\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eOther Features to Consider\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe\u0026rsquo;

2385ve talked about bathtubs\u0026rsquo;

2386 sizes, shapes, and materials, but now it\u0026rsquo;

2387s time to cover a few other features that affect your bathtub. If you would like a bathtub with a bit more support for your back while relaxing, try out a bathtub with lumbar support. If you are looking for a spa-like tub, you can purchase a bathtub with jets or a heated surface. You will also want to decide with what material you would like to finish your bathtub. The most common finish is a high-gloss white finish.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2388\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eDrain Stopper\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAlong with the features listed above, you\u0026rsquo;

2389ll want to think about the drain stopper you would like. There are five drain stoppers:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eToe-Touch: \u003c/strong\u003eYou can open and close the train with the touch of your toe\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePush-Pull: \u003c/strong\u003eThe traditional pull-up knob in the middle to push it down and pull it to open\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFlip-It: \u003c/strong\u003eYou flip a toggle that will open or close, and you move the toggle from side to side\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePop-Up: \u003c/strong\u003eAn internal rod moves to raise or lower the stopper\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTrip-Lever:\u003c/strong\u003e An internal plunger stops water flow in the drain\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAll of these drain stoppers are great options, so the one that you decide for your new tub will be up to you and your personal preference.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2943"css":"","html":"\u003ch2\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFind the Ideal Bathtub\u0026nbsp;

2944\u003c/strong\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2945\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eVevano Home offers a wide selection of\u0026nbsp;

2946high-quality, stylish bathtubs in various\u0026nbsp;

2947sizes and materials. Whether you\u0026#39;

2948re looking for a timeless cast iron freestanding tub or a sleek modern drop-in, we\u0026#39;

2949ve got you covered. Not sure what tub is best for you? We can help with that too! Here\u0026#39;

2950s everything you need to know about tub sizes, shapes, materials, and more\u0026nbsp;

2951so you can find the ideal tub for your bathroom.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2952\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eBathtub Size\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLet\u0026rsquo;

2953s start with the size of your bathtub. Some may prefer an above-average length instead of a deeper soaking depth. If you are a tall person that enjoys laying back and relaxing in your tub, you may want to choose a length over depth. Bathtubs come in 4ft, 5ft, and 6ft lengths.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOn the other hand, if you prefer to have a deeper bathtub, allowing you to emerge yourself in the water fully, you will probably want to prioritize depth over length. Some people also enjoy deeper tubs because their kids or pets can fit inside as well. A standard bathtub measures 14\u0026ndash;

295420 inches. Whatever you prefer, there is an option for you, and our guide on \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/resource-center/standard-tub-size-measurement-guide/\"\u003ehow to measure a bathtub\u003c/a\u003e can help!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2955\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eTypes of Bathtubs\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAs you search for a new tub, it helps to understand the five main types of bathtubs\u0026mdash;

2956drop-in, alcove, freestanding, whirlpool, and walk-in bathtubs. All of these bathtubs are very different and have unique features.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2957\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2958\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/showers-and-tubs-drop-in-bathtubs/\"\u003eDrop-in Bathtub\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis particular type of bathtub is your typical rectangular-shaped bathtub with angular lines. Drop-in bathtubs are tubs dropped in a frame or structure, featuring a rim that goes around the top of the tub. You can customize your drop-in bathtub by selecting the material you would like the rim to be made of;

2959 most people prefer tile or stone. These bathtubs are ideal for a children\u0026rsquo;

2960s bathroom because of its shape and ease of getting in and out.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2961\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2962\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/showers-tubs-alcove-bathtubs/\"\u003eAlcove Bathtub\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAn alcove bathtub is most known to be in the corner of a bathroom and is known for the way it is installed. These beautiful bathtubs are installed into a recess in a bathroom, often against a wall or in the corner. Since these tubs are designed to fit between three furnished walls, it\u0026rsquo;

2963s not uncommon to see a shower curtain on the fourth wall. Alcove tubs and drop-in tubs are very similar;

2964 however, alcove tubs require fewer steps during installation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2965\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2966\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/showers-and-tubs-freestanding-bathtubs/\"\u003eFreestanding Bathtub\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/resource-center/best-freestanding-tubs/\"\u003eFreestanding bathtubs\u003c/a\u003e are all the rave these days. Freestanding bathtubs add a modern or contemporary look to your bathroom, making it look sleek and updated. However, if you\u0026rsquo;

2967re going for an antique-looking freestanding tub, clawfoot bathtubs would be a great option.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2968\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2969\"\u003eWhirlpool Bathtubs\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA whirlpool bathtub is known for its jets that help relax and massage the muscles. So if you\u0026rsquo;

2970re looking for a relaxing bathing experience, this may be the tub for you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2971\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2972\"\u003eWalk-in Bathtubs\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis type of tub is designed for those who have trouble getting in and out of a regular bathtub. Walk-in bathtubs have grab bars that help avoid hazards like slipping and falling. Seats are also commonly found in this type of bathtub because they take pressure off the legs. A walk-in bathtub is different because there is more vertical space in the tub instead of horizontal space.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2973\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eBathtub Materials\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThere are various materials that bathtubs are made out of, but we will cover three of the most common materials here. These materials include porcelain, fiberglass, and acrylic. It\u0026rsquo;

2974s essential to understand the characteristics of each material so that you know \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/resource-center/how-to-clean-a-bathtub/\"\u003ehow to clean your bathtub \u003c/a\u003eand how best to maintain it over time. For a deeper dive into bathtub materials, check out our \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/resource-center/best-bathtub-materials/\"\u003ebest bathtub materials\u003c/a\u003e comparison article.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2975\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2976\"\u003eSteel Bathtubs\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSteel bathtubs are sometimes referred to as porcelain tubs because the steel is covered in porcelain enamel. (On a similar note, cast iron tubs are also typically covered in porcelain, which is why they are known as enameled cast iron tubs.) Steel tubs generally are well-protected by this porcelain enamel, which is both stain and scratch-resistant and easy to clean. However, steel tubs don\u0026rsquo;

2977t retain heat well and are prone to chipping if a heavy object falls on its surface.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2978\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2979\"\u003eCast Iron Bathtubs\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThough one of the heaviest tubs you can buy, enameled cast iron tubs are incredibly durable, resistant to stains, scratches, and chips. Cast iron tubs are especially known for their excellent heat retention. With proper maintenance, your cast iron tub can last you for decades to come.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2980\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2981\"\u003eFiberglass Bathtubs\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFiberglass tubs are made from fiberglass-reinforced plastic molded into the shape of a bathtub. These tubs are coated with a layer of gelcoat resin, which provides a high-quality finish and makes the surface easy to clean. Fiberglass is also a lightweight material, making it easy to move and install your tub.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, due to the nature of this lightweight material, fiberglass is also one of the most brittle bathtub materials on the market, cracking often. As a result, fiberglass tubs are generally less expensive than porcelain and acrylic tubs. In addition, the use of standard cleaning products on fiberglass also tends to discolor the surface over time. So, although this is one of the least expensive bathtub materials, keep in mind the long-term cost of buying a fiberglass tub.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2982\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003e\u003cspan style=\"font-size:18px;

2983\"\u003eAcrylic Bathtubs\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAcrylic is a combination of materials like stabilizers, resins, and fillers. Acrylic is often reinforced with fiberglass, making it a bit pricier than fiberglass tubs but more durable. In addition, acrylic is a non-porous material, which means that it will not absorb any excess water in your bathtub, helping it to avoid cracking. This non-porous material also helps with heat retention, keeping the water in your tub warmer for longer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2984\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eOther Features to Consider\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe\u0026rsquo;

2985ve talked about bathtubs\u0026rsquo;

2986 sizes, shapes, and materials, but now it\u0026rsquo;

2987s time to cover a few other features that affect your bathtub. If you would like a bathtub with a bit more support for your back while relaxing, try out a bathtub with lumbar support. If you are looking for a spa-like tub, you can purchase a bathtub with jets or a heated surface. You will also want to decide with what material you would like to finish your bathtub. The most common finish is a high-gloss white finish.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

2988\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eDrain Stopper\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAlong with the features listed above, you\u0026rsquo;

2989ll want to think about the drain stopper you would like. There are five drain stoppers:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eToe-Touch: \u003c/strong\u003eYou can open and close the train with the touch of your toe\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePush-Pull: \u003c/strong\u003eThe traditional pull-up knob in the middle to push it down and pull it to open\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFlip-It: \u003c/strong\u003eYou flip a toggle that will open or close, and you move the toggle from side to side\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePop-Up: \u003c/strong\u003eAn internal rod moves to raise or lower the stopper\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTrip-Lever:\u003c/strong\u003e An internal plunger stops water flow in the drain\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAll of these drain stoppers are great options, so the one that you decide for your new tub will be up to you and your personal preference.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;
